A complete, ship-ready extension passes validate (exit 0). The env is pinned inline
so the transcript is deterministic on any machine: ABLETON_APP points at a
non-existent app (no Live detected → the host-apiVersion rule skips), RACKABEL_HOME
is isolated, and git config is suppressed (so author inference is not consulted).
With no prior pack recorded, the version-bump rule also skips-with-note.

```
$ ABLETON_APP=/nonexistent-ableton-live.app RACKABEL_HOME=rk-home GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL=/dev/null GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM=/dev/null rackabel validate
[✓] manifest complete
[!] minimumApiVersion 1.0.0 — skipped (no Ableton Live found to compare against)
[!] version 1.2.0 — skipped (no previous pack recorded; this is the first release)
[✓] CHANGELOG.md has an entry for 1.2.0
[!] native dependencies — none declared
[!] stable-identifier drift — not checkable yet (command ids are registered in code, not the manifest; see `rackabel explain RK4005`)
all checks passed

